The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | ADRs plunge 17%
                                                                                                               ADRs plunge 17%
                            
	New York, April 13 (PTI): The American Depositary Receipts of Satyam today plunged nearly 17 per cent within minutes of opening on the New York Stock Exchange, after Tech Mahindra emerged as the highest bidder for a controlling stake in the fraud-hit firm.        
	Satyam ADRs plunged to a low of $2.20, down 16.98 per cent from its previous close of $2.65. The ADRs were later trading down 12.83 per cent at $2.31 in morning trade on the NYSE.                                                                                                                                        
